### HYMN XCV

#### An incantation against an undetected thief

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0709501">1</span></span>To heaven,
as 'twere, have soared this man's two vultures,  
   staggering, dusky hued.  
  The Parcher and the Drier-up, the pair who parch and dry his  
   heart.  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0709502">2</span></span>I verily
have stirred them up like oxen resting after toil.  
  Like two loud-snarling curs, or like two wolves who watch to  
   make their spring:  
<span class="margnote"><span id="an_0709503">3</span></span>Like two
that thrust, like two that pierce, like two that strike  
   with mutual blows.  
  I bind the conduit of the man or dame who hence hath taken  
   aught.

